    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using Ctrl+V to perform a blockwise (visual block) selection of multiple full-width characters, then yanking (pressing y) and pasting (pressing p), the pasted text appears correctly, but immediately followed by a number of spaces equal to the length of the yanked block. This issue was introduced in commit cdf848a314, as confirmed by git bisect.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nPrepare a text file containing full-width characters, for example:\nあいうえお\n\nOpen Neovim with clipboard support:\n```nvim --clean --cmd \":set clipboard=unnamedplus\" full-width.txt```\nEnter blockwise visual mode with Ctrl+V, then select multiple full-width characters (e.g., \"あい\").\nYank the selection with y.\nPaste with P.\n\nAfter pasting, extra spaces are inserted immediately after the pasted text, equal in number to the yanked block's length.\n\nFor example:\nあい  あいうえお\n\nwith two spaces after \"あい\".\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe pasted text should be inserted without additional spaces.\n\nFor example, selecting \"あい\" and pasting should produce:\nあいあいうえお\n\nwith no extra spaces after \"あい\".\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.4-dev-7+ge534afa5ab\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.1582\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24.04 6.8.0-64-generic \n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME Terminal 3.52.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
